# Some notes generated while developing shopping store using Python

# If the user inputs " mobile phones ", .strip() will remove the leading and trailing spaces, resulting in "mobile phones".

# The .lower() method in Python converts all characters in a string to lowercase.

# Example:

# User input: " MoBile PHonEs "
# After .strip(): "MoBile PHonEs"
# After .lower(): "mobile phones"

# Using 'in' in if and elif statements makes the code more efficient 
# and easier to maintain, especially when checking against multiple potential matches.